"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-06-paris-2024-olympics-ogazi-races-into-mens-400m-final\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Samuel Ogazi breezed into men's 400m final at the 2024 Olympic Games on Tuesday night, DAILY POST reports.  Ogazi came third in Heat 3 of the men's semi-final.  The debutant ran a personal best time of 44.41s.  Great Britain's Matthew Hudson-Smith won the race in a time of 44.07s, while Michael Norman came in second in a time of 44.26s.  Ogazi is the first Nigerian athlete to qualify for the men's 400m final in 36 years.  Innocent Egbunike was the last Nigerian to achieve the feat.  The final of the event will hold on Thursday.  UCL: Dessers rescues draw for Rangers against Dynamo Kiev  Niger Tornadoes chief lists requirements for successful NPFL campaign  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"